{title:Bivariate mixed Poisson regression (using Maximum Simulated Likelihood)}

{phang}
{cmd:bimpoisson} {hline 2} Bivariate mixed Poisson regression (MSL)

{marker syntax}{...}
{title:Syntax}

{p 8 17 2}
{cmd:bimpoisson}
{it:{help depvar:depvar1}} {it:{help depvar:depvar2}}
[{indepvars}]
{ifin}
[{it:{help weight}}]{cmd:,} 
[{it:{help options}}]

{p 4 4 2}can be used when {it:indepvars} is a common set of predictors 
for each dependent variable. For this case, and also situations where the sets
of predictors for each dependent variable differ, the following syntax can be
used:

{p 8 17 2}
{cmd:bimpoisson}
{it:equation1} {it:equation2}
{ifin}
[{it:{help weight}}]{cmd:,} 
[{it:{help options}}]

{p 4 4 2}where {it:equation1} and {it:equation2} are each specified as

{p 12 12 2}{cmd:(} [{it:eqname}{cmd::}] {it:{help depvar}} [{cmd:=}] [{indepvars}] {cmd:)}
		
{p 4 4 2}{cmd:bimpoisson} shares the features of all estimation commands; see help
{help est}.

{p 4 4 2}{cmd:bimpoisson} typed without arguments redisplays the last estimates. 

