{phang}
{opt collinear}, {opt coeflegend}; see {helpb estimation options:[R] Estimation options}.


{marker examples}{...}
{title:Examples}

{p 4 4 2}
The examples below are based on the data about numbers of doctor and hospital
visits and their predictors accompanying the {cmd:bivcnto} package 
by Xu and Hardin (2016). The data are downloadable via the commands {stata "net sj 16-2 st0433"} and
{stata "net get st0433"}. MT's empirical application is based on data previously
 used by Deb and Trivedi (1997): see "debtrivedi.dta". (We downloaded these 
 data from the {it: Journal of Applied Econometrics} archive website 
 and converted them to Stata format.)

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: use "rwm1984.dta", clear}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: correlate docvis hospvis}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: generate byte postHS = edlevel1 == 0}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: generate byte MarM = (married == 1 & female == 0)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: generate byte MarF = (married == 1 & female == 1)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: generate byte SinM = (married == 0 & female == 0)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: generate byte SinF = (married == 0 & female == 1)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: global xvars MarM SinM SinF kids outwork postHS}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: * 400 uniform draws & antithetics, bias correction}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: bimpoisson docvis hospvis $xvars, robust ///}

{p 8 8 2}{cmd: seed(13159) nsim(400) bias antithetic}	

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: matrix b1 = e(b) }

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: * increase # sims (800)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: bimpoisson docvis hospvis $xvars, robust ///}

{p 8 8 2}{cmd: seed(4321) from(b1) nsim(800) bias antithetic}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: * same again, but with Halton draws}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: bimpoisson docvis hospvis $xvars, robust halton ///}

{p 8 8 2}{cmd: from(b1) nsim(800) bias} 

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: * alternative approach (not using sampling function)}

{p 4 8 2}{cmd: bimpoisson docvis hospvis $xvars, robust halton alt ///}

{p 8 8 2}{cmd: nsim(400) bias}

{marker stored_results}{...}
{title:Stored results}

{p 4 4 2} In addition to the usual results saved after {cmd:ml},
{cmd:bimpoisson} also saves the following in e():

{p2col 5 15 19 2: Scalars}{p_end}
{synoptset 15 tabbed}{...}
{synopt:{cmd:e(nsims)}} number of simulations used to calculate the
simulated log-likelihood{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(sigma1)}} estimate of sigma1{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(sigma1_se)}} estimate of the standard error of sigma1{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(sigma2)}} estimate of sigma1{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(sigma2_se)}} estimate of the standard error of sigma2{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(rho)}} estimate of rho{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(rho_se)}} estimate of the standard error of rho{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(antithetic)}} 1 if {cmd:antithetic} option used, 0 otherwise{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(halton)}} 1 if {cmd:halton} option used, 0 otherwise{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(burn)}} value of # set by {cmd:burn(#)} option{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(bias)}} 1 if {cmd:bias} option used, 0 otherwise{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(rho_sf)}} value of # set by {cmd:rho_sf(#)} option{p_end}
{synopt:{cmd:e(rng0)}} 1 if {cmd:rng0} option used; 0 otherwise{p_end}

{p2col 5 15 19 2: Macros}{p_end}
{synoptset 15 tabbed}{...}
{synopt:{cmd:e(seed)}} contains the seed set by the {cmd:seed} option if 
specified. If seed not set, contains "seed not set"{p_end}

